    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/34586#discussion_r2171397435\n\nThe current `:connect` impl #34257 does not handle failure.\n\nBecause the server may be on another machine, the server itself can't decide whether a `:connect` address is valid.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n### Phase 1\n\nIf the UI fails to connect,\n\n- show an error\n    - the message should mention the address of the old server\n    - but the UI doesn't know if the old server is still running...\n\n### Phase 2 (optional)\n\nThe UI could do more complex things like try to reattach to the old server and raise an error via rpc `request('nvim_echo', { ... })`.",
